cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with geometric objects (lines and rays) and their optimization problems (TSP and shortest path).
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents linear-time approximation algorithms for the TSPN and TSP problems.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the TSP and TSPN problems are classic combinatorial optimization problems.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses approximation ratios for the TSPN and TSP problems.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the TSP problem has applications in network routing and optimization.
